The paper deals with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for 3D facial shape representation, generation, and translation, which are primarily computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with mesh convolutions for deep networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also presents an extensive series of qualitative and quantitative experiments, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with 3D shape analysis, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper presents a novel GAN-based method for 3D facial shape representation, generation, and translation, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
